==Description==

The '''TechDraw SurfaceFinishSymbols''' tool adds a surface finish symbol to a page.

[[Image:TechDraw_SurfaceFinishSymbolExample1.png|330px]]
{{Caption|The task panel with the ISO style selected. On the right the created symbol.}}

[[Image:TechDraw_SurfaceFinishSymbolExample2.png|330px]]
{{Caption|The task panel with the ASME style selected. On the right the created symbol.}}

==Usage==

# Select an existing view.
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:TechDraw_SurfaceFinishSymbols.svg|16px]] [[TechDraw_SurfaceFinishSymbols|Create a Surface Finish Symbol]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|TechDraw → Symbols → [[Image:TechDraw_SurfaceFinishSymbols.svg|16px]] Create a Surface Finish Symbol}} option from the menu.
# A task panel opens.
# Specify the required symbol by clicking one of the 6 symbol buttons.
# Optionally change the {{MenuCommand|Symbol angle}}.
# Select the {{MenuCommand|ISO}} or the {{MenuCommand|ASME}} style.
# Select and/or enter the required attributes.
# Press the {{Button|OK}} button.


